cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the connectivity of the Internet and the use of directed graphs to represent how destinations propagate through the network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the effects of network operator policies on the connectivity of the Internet, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of directed graphs and numerical analyses could also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
